Author: Eugene@SB
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Ladies and Gentlemen,  Starbase will begin our launch roll out with the release of the project submission page!  http:// bit. ly/Starbase_SubmissionBCT  The link above is unique to the Bitcoin Talk channel; similar links will be applied to Wechat, Facebook and the Platform page. This is for analytics purposes so that we know which avenue is best to reach the most people.  From this data, we will adjust our marketing accordingly for effectiveness.  Once we gather feedback from you about the project submissions and improved on it where applicable, the next launch phase will be the release of the platform proper with a speech from our Project Manager and Founder; by then we shall have more marketing in place and more people to participate to trade STAR, in turn, that should increase the STAR value.  Our final phase of the launch will be an official ceremony and with projects on the platform, we will make waves all over the internet.  *The reason for this launch strategy is to make it a launch like a rocket: a sustained burn and stretch our marketing window to create more content for more attention.*  We now invite everyone to click on our links and spread it out to people that you know with great ideas!  Once again, thank you and we look forward to your feedback at the different launch phases!  #SkyrocketYourIdea @StarbaseCo

Author: Cryptocurrencies News
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Latest development update of Starbase platform: UX improvements  https://blog.starbase.co/progress-report-ux-b2510bad7e16   Will present here:   New Metamask alerts — A new alert was created in order to better inform the user i.e: if the user is connected on the Testnet instead of the Mainnet, we will block the user and alert him with a Metamask error modal advising him to change to the Mainnet. New friendly URLs for the projects pages — We have modified our URLs to the following format: starbase.co/projects/super-awesome-project. What does it mean for the Starbase users and Project Owners? Project pages are easy to remember; quick way to share wherever you want, improving user engagement sharing in conference talks, commercial presentations and so on; improved SEO; and it's simple and beautiful, isn’t it? New humanized errors — New alerts and modals were implemented with support in multiple languages in order to improve the UX. A better KYC form description —We have labeled the KYC sections in order to make the process as transparent as possible for users and investors, avoiding any confusion during the whole KYC process. Other improvements KYC form reviewed in order to avoid any way to skip the verification steps; Metamask lib updated to avoid that any function be deprecated in the near future; Integrated Sentry with the most critical routines and features. So that’s it for now. I apologize for not sharing details about the Stake feature yet, we’ve decided to keep the suspense a bit longer. As soon as possible I will return with all the details.

Author: Easy2Mine
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: STARBASE NEWS  January 30th 2018  Starbase was a proud participant and sponsor of the St Moritz Crypto Finance Conference, which took place January 17–19 in Switzerland.  CFC18 is the world’s largest investor conference on cryptocurrencies and blockchain investments, bringing together both private and institutional investors and the leading providers of the crypto & blockchain universe.  Tomoaki Sato, the CEO, presented the "Starbase Solution" at the conference. The team met with several companies and cryptofunds who are looking to invest in projects, and with people and companies who are interested in launching their project ICO on the platform.  Starbase team at CFC with: Cybertrust (top left), Bitcoin Suisse (top right), MME (bottom right), and cryptofund Upvest (bottom left).  Alpha testers Starbase has selected community members to support our product. They will help us with the platform's quality assurance. on the road to the beta release (estimated to be ready in one month). Testing will begin early february.  Alpha platform features We are in the approval stage of this new features that are going to be delivered to the alpha testers:  API upgrades and microservices architecture adopted  UI changes to improve performance  A brand new UX for mobile users  A  KYC/AML process to verify user identity

For example, imagine a person from Brazil, where the annual interest rate can reach 60%, wants to borrow money from a person in Japan where the annual yield might be 1%. Author: Tonisim
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: P2P blockchain-based lending platforms, Lendoit x Starbase for “socializing loss”  The P2P lending market P2P lending platforms have existed for quite a while now, and have an expected growth rate of 50% each year until 2020 according to several researches. The centralized way banks and other institutional bodies currently handle loans all over the world leave no choice to the masses but to look for alternatives. This problem is escalating, pushing a lot of companies in the race for providing alternatives. So far many have tried but many issues remain. Lendoit wants to solve the two principal issues:  (1) these companies are offering Fiat money loans, making themselves subject to regulation and thus remaining centralized, and (2) being regulated and dealing with Fiat requires these companies to operate under a certain jurisdiction only, preventing them from arbitrating the different interest around the globe in favour of the loan parties.  Enters the Blockchain: using cryptocurrencies we can allow two people anywhere on the globe to interact without the need for an intermediate, making them find the sweet spot between the different interest rates in their country. For example, imagine a person from Brazil, where the annual interest rate can reach 60%, wants to borrow money from a person in Japan where the annual yield might be 1%. If we will let them negotiate the terms themselves eventually they will reach an agreement around 30% which offers both parties an extremely beneficial deal.  https://blog.starbase.co/p2p-blockchain-based-lending-platforms-lendoit-x-starbase-for-socializing-loss-fe4d0252688b

Author: bircoin
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: STAR Token sale report & withdrawal guide Short summary STAR token Address: 0xf70a642bd387f94380ffb90451c2c81d4eb82cbc Total amount of CNY raised during token sale: 59,339,496 CNY Total amount of circulating STAR (including early purchasers, and bounty): 187.5M STAR Founders and early contributors: 62.5M STAR (1 year lock up+ 1/52 transferable per year) Starbase company: 750M STAR (Only 100M STAR per year become transferable for further fundings) STAR Withdrawal instruction STAR token amount calculation depends on the value we raised, therefore you need to withdraw STAR from the STAR withdrawal contract on the website: https://starbase.co/crowdsale. Please look at the section 3 “How to withdraw my STAR Tokens” from the user guide made by Ernane Luis below.  In order to withdraw from imToken like wallet which has “Advanced send” functionality, you can withdraw by sending transaction with these parameters. to: 0x54c548703c6f423cf7ed22806b608d332fcebb3b value: 0 gas: 200,000 data: 0xbecd7027 And if you participated from BitcoinSuisse https://www.bitcoinsuisse.ch/starbase-ico/, please wait for their instructions. Starbase Roadmap and next Here’s our development roadmap blog post. Our platform official launch is scheduled for Jan-Feb 2018. We will accept pre-registrations for projects and supporters. Special thanks to BitcoinSuisse & PICOPS team Special thank to BitcoinSuisse team for clear and detailed token sale support to fit KYC requirements for Starbase. https://www.bitcoinsuisse.ch/starbase-ico/ And thanks to the PICOPS team for supporting us and guiding users to use PICOPS for STAR token sale, and for planning the cooperation for KYC checks for future token sales. https://picops.parity.io/ Thank you for your support  https://blog.starbase.co/star-token-sale-report-withdrawal-guide-1c6a3833acc9

Author: lordzc
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Below are some of the questions we received related to withdrawing the STAR Token. If you continue to have problems withdrawing your tokens.  Please reach out to support@starbase.co   How to withdraw STAR Token?  A: The STAR tokens are available for withdraw now. In order to get you STAR tokens you  must send a transaction which call a function to our smart contract.  Please follow the guide or the video tutorial.  For imToken or Exodus or any wallet that do not support interaction with smart contract, you should export the keystore and import to MyEtherWallet. Please check the User Guide.  UserGuide: https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/assets-cdn.starbase.co/docs/2017/11/STAR_User+Guide_latest.pdf  Video :  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DDFvmP88Hq4  ABI information:   https://etherscan.io/address/0x54c548703c6f423cf7ed22806b608d332fcebb3b#code  I called the withdraw Function but I didn’t get STARs. Now what?  A: You must withdrawal using the same address that you made the contribution.  I’m Getting invalid ABI, what to do?  A: If you use the ABI from the user guide and it's not working, copy the ABI from Smart Contract on  Etherscan by following this tutorial:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DDFvmP88Hq4  https://etherscan.io/address/0x54c548703c6f423cf7ed22806b608d332fcebb3b#code  I made my contribution using the imToken app, how can I withdraw from ImToken?  A: You have to export the keystore from you Exodus account and import it to the MyEtherWallet app. IN this way MyEtherWallet will have access of you address and you will be able to follow the tutorial.  Please follow our user guide https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/assets-cdn.starbase.co/docs/2017/11/STAR_User+Guide_latest.pdf  Why I can’t transfer my STAR tokens?  A: Tokens will only be transferrable in two weeks.

Author: maddox7
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: let me summarize for you guys so far they have collected USD 8m (of USD 10m hardcap) in total: USD 1m: early investors USD 2m: pre-sale through Bitcoin Suisse USD 5m: pre-sale through Bitcoin Suisse (part 2)  The reason for a 2nd pre-sale through Bitcoin Suisse was because USD 5m was already raised through two partners (based in China) which has been cancelled afterwards due to China's ICO ban. The amount has been returned to the investors which led to a delay of the whole crowdsale.  Now USD 2m (10m - 8m) is left for public crowdsale, exact date will be announced by end of this week as they are currently looking for a good KYC/AML solution first in order to avoid any problems with the Swiss regulations in future.  Slack has been closed to new user registrations due to a lot of scam attacks. But they will move to Rocket chat on Friday 27.10.17 11am GMT. https://blog.starbase.co/announcing-our-migration-to-rocket-chat-1bae5f7fa8a0  Official website: https://starbase.co/ Blog: https://blog.starbase.co/  Hope this helps

Author: thew3apon
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Starbase Token Crowdsale Postponed until   September 5, 2017 00:00 UTC    Starbase’s crowdsale that was schedule for August 30th 2017 has been reschedule to September 5th 2017 00:00 UTC.  There are a few reasons why we decided to reschedule the sale.  Starbase is relocating from Singapore to Switzerland. The company’s establishment in Switzerland was schedule to be completed on August 29th but after weeks preparing the documentation and having everything in order, our legal team informed us that the name we submitted on our application is no longer available. They are expediting the process to complete the process with the new name this week. Starbase as a company is not allow to accept funds (ETH, BTC, Fiat) until the company has been registered properly in Switzerland. Secondly, without a registered name, we had to delay the pre-crowdsale transfers from our partners.  The partners are aware of the situation and supported the decision.  To address the issue with the rising ETH price and the crowdsale low cap, we have decided to fixed the ETH price at 2390 CNY for the pre-crowdsale purchases using the average on August 29, 2017, as agreed in the original agreement with our partners.   We are also in the process of a 3rd party audit of the smart contract.  This will assure the development of the contract is following best practices, help identify any security issues, if any and provides a transparent view to our community.   We apologies for the delay and will continue working toward starting the crowdsale on September 5th.   Best Regards, Starbase Team

Author: amintek15
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Dear STAR Early Purchasers  Thank you for supporting Starbase as early purchasers and actively endorsing us on social media channels.  Last week, the Starbase team has discussed possible regulatory implications of the STAR token with MME, our legal partner in Switzerland, which is specialized in blockchain matters and the conduct of TGE’s. (Token Generation Event).  Due to the current boom of TGE’s all around the world, national regulators will be reviewing closer the involved business models. "Revenue/profit right" tokens may be classified as "securities" in certain jurisdictions. We already received such an opinion from a Singapore law firm.  If the STAR tokens are classified as securities, STAR tokens will have less liquidity, because most exchanges will not list STAR tokens and serious international regulatory challenges may arise for Starbase company and platform, which even could result in the delay or complete default of the release of the Starbase platform.  So after days of internal discussions with MME and within the team regarding the risks and liabilities connected to the revenue function of the STAR token, the Starbase team decided to remove this revenue function.  However, as it is an important aspect of the project that STAR token users benefit from their engagement, the revenue function will be replaced by other attractive functionalities, including new feature of priority and/or discount of token purchase by staking and payment rights for bounty campaign system as a service for project owners.  STAR token holders who stakes STAR tokens to staking contract can priority and /or discount purchase projects tokens issued and sold on Starbase platform.  “Stake” means locking up tokens to a contract in a certain period of time, so stake mechanism will make less supply, and more needs for STAR Tokens.  Please find here our renewed draft of the token terms and condition: https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/assets-cdn.starbase.co/docs/2017/07/Starbase_token_terms_v13.pdf Please look up the "Regulatory Risk" para 37 also.  As per the renewed draft of the token terms and condition, a reward input functionality may be implemented in the future. We will assess this option depending on the blockchain token regulatory landscape.  Our goal is to best serve our stakeholders’ interest and financial objectives.  If you have any questions or opinions, please let us know.  If you don't reply within two weeks from now, you will be considered as agreeing on the new token terms and condition.  Best, Starbase Early Purchase Team    After big changes like this in theory I can demand to get back my ETH no ? someone can help me maybe ? It's a nice project but that was the first reason I invest in...

There are some wrong records at early purchase contract, so we will publish early purchase amendment contract, and will have some removal of early purchase records and some of early purchases records' address change. Author: romanekras
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Starbase is a user-centric global crowdfunding and token payment platform which connects people who want to develop challenging projects like startup companies or other kinds of innovative ideas with people like investors, engineers, designers, or marketers who want to support these projects all over the world. By using Starbase, innovative people can launch their ideas by sharing long-term incentives with collaborators. This is much faster, reaches a global scale, comes at a low transaction cost, and investors can individually commit a small amount of money. There are already more than 650 blockchain tokens in the world, with a 25 billion usd market cap. We make it easy for you to create a new token, so join them and get funded.More

Author: iqbal26
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Terms:  1: Users are not allowed to remove the signature During the campaign period.. removing campaign in that period will be result of No Payment. 2: User must do a minimum of 50 posts. Less than 50 posts will not get paid. 3: Spam, Low Quality and Off topic posts will not be counted for payment. 4: One account Per User. using multiple accounts and cheating the bounty is not allowed, user found to be cheating with any form of bounty will be permanently blacklisted.  For rules detail you can read here https://blog.starbase.co/starbase-blog-bitcointalk-bounty-program-v-1-ae96d28ef498

Author: romanekras
Title: ** Starbase ** Token Based Global Crowdfunding and Crowdsourcing Platform **
Body: Starbase to Revolutionize the Crowdfunding Market with Its Blockchain Offering   In the age of shared economy, innovative projects do not have to rely on institutional investors to raise the required funds. If an idea is attractive enough for the general public, they can contribute towards the idea to make it a reality. The introduction of crowdfunding platforms as a mean to support ideas is now possible. Most of such platforms are currently tied to traditional models. They deal in fiat currencies, and therefore limit their global outreach. Starbase, on the other hand, is a crowdfunding platform which exclusively relies on blockchain to bypass territorial limitations. The cryptocurrency-based crowdfunding/crowdsourcing platform is founded by Tomoaki Sato, a blockchain engineer. The platform allows startups and individual project creators to list their product ideas and goals, to raise funds from the diverse cryptocurrency community. Starbase supports a range of cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, Ethereum, etc., to make it easier for both the contributors as well as the project owners to send/receive transactions. Even institutional investors, VC firms, angel investors can become part of the Starbase community and invest in projects.
